# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AWS Deploy Kit - Secret Schema
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file declares what secrets your application needs in SSM Parameter Store.
# Copy to 'deploy-secrets' and edit the list for your app:
#   cp deploy-secrets.example deploy-secrets
#
# FORMAT:
#   One secret name per line. Comments (#) and blank lines are ignored.
#   All secrets are stored as SecureString in SSM.
#
# NOTE:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables are NOT listed here. They are build-time args
#   that get baked into the Next.js client bundle during docker build.
#   See deploy-build-args / deploy-build-args.example for those.
#
# USAGE:
#   Interactive setup (prompts for each value):
#     ./bin/secrets.sh setup
#
#   Bulk import from a .env-style file:
#     ./bin/secrets.sh import deploy-secrets.values
#
#   The .values file format is KEY=VALUE, one per line.
#   NEVER commit .values files -- they contain real secrets.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GAB / Ignatius API
GAB_API_URL
GAB_CLIENT_ID

# GAB authentication token flow
AUTH_TOKEN_URL
AUTH_TOKEN_METHOD
AUTH_TOKEN_BODY_MODE
AUTH_TOKEN_HEADERS_JSON
AUTH_TOKEN_BODY_FORM_JSON
AUTH_TOKEN_RESPONSE_PATH

# Ignatius service account (anonymous proxy)
IGNATIUS_USERNAME
IGNATIUS_PASSWORD
IGNATIUS_CLIENT_ID

# Ignatius admin service account
IGNATIUS_ADMIN_USERNAME
IGNATIUS_ADMIN_PASSWORD
IGNATIUS_ADMIN_CLIENT_ID

# Ignatius app identity
IGNATIUS_APP_TOKEN
IGNATIUS_CONSTITUENT_ROLE
IGNATIUS_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN

# reCAPTCHA v3 (server-side secret)
RECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY

# AI / third-party keys
OPENAI_API_KEY
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
